data.title: My Code launches Remezcla Más, streaming platform for Latine Gen Z & Millennials with 10,000+ hours of content.
data.description: A new platform has launched in Los Angeles on October 30, 2025, featuring over 10,000 hours of content spanning TV shows, Films, and other entertainment options. This platform builds upon My Code's existing video offerings and introduces new FAST and AVOD channels. With a strong reputation for cultural influence and success in the streaming industry, this expansion solidifies the platform's position as a leader in providing diverse and extensive entertainment choices to viewers.

data.title: Carvana's shares fall as analysts debate growth rate vs. margin pressures. Needham sets $500 target, BTIG $450. Unit growth at 9%. EBITDA down sequentially. Fourth quarter guidance predicts growth slowdown.
data.description: Carvana Co (CVNA) saw its stock prices decrease after revealing its third-quarter results. Analyst Chris Pierce from Needham maintained a Buy rating with a target of $500 while Marvin Fong from BTIG reiterated a Buy rating with a target of $450. Carvana showed a 9% unit growth exceeding expectations, but its adjusted EBITDA per retail unit declined sequentially. The fourth-quarter guidance indicates a potential slowdown from current growth rates. For more details, the complete article is accessible on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Meta Platforms, Inc. stock drops 10% after Q3 earnings. Reported revenue of $51.24B beats estimates. EPS at $1.05 (adjusted $7.25). Capital expenditure expected $70-72B for 2025.
data.description: META Platforms, Inc. (NASDAQ: META) saw a decline in shares on Thursday after disclosing its third-quarter earnings. The company reported diluted earnings per share of $1.05, inclusive of a one-time, non-cash income tax charge of $15.93 billion, falling below estimates of $6.68. Adjusted earnings per share stood at $7.25. Revenue for the quarter was reported at $51.24 billion, surpassing estimates of $49.39 billion. Following the report, Meta shares dropped approximately 10%. The decrease is attributed partially to increased spending, with projected capital expenditures for 2025 expected to range between $70 billion and $72 billion, up from earlier guidance of $66 billion to $72 billion.

data.title: Fox Corp announced a $1.5 billion buyback after their fiscal first-quarter revenue hit $3.74 billion, up 5% from last year. Share rose on the news.
data.description: Shares of Fox Corp. (NASDAQ: FOX) and (NASDAQ: FOXA) surged following the release of their fiscal first-quarter 2026 results, with revenue climbing by 5% year over year to $3.74 billion, surpassing last year's $3.56 billion. This performance exceeded Wall Street's projection of $3.57 billion. Adjusted net income also saw growth, reaching $686 million, or $1.51 per share, exceeding analysts' forecast of $1.08 per share. This marked an improvement from $672 million, or $1.45 per share, recorded in the previous year. The positive results were primarily driven by increases in advertising and streaming revenue. For further details, the full article is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Report from Kuick Research reveals 800 ADC candidates in global Cancer Antibody Drug Conjugates market; opportunity >USD 70 billion by 2031.
data.description: Kuick Research has released a 1300-page report on the Global Cancer Antibody Drug Conjugate (ADC) Market, providing valuable insights for investors and stakeholders in the biopharmaceutical sector. The report identifies over 800 ADC candidates in clinical development, categorized by various criteria such as clinical phase, indication, and sponsoring company. The market is projected to exceed USD 70 billion by 2031, with continuous growth anticipated till 2031. This report serves as a strategic tool for investors to navigate the evolving competitive landscape and spot potential acquisition targets. For detailed information, the full story is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: CPV & Texas Energy Fund secure $1.1B loan to build 1,350 MW natural gas power plant in Texas. Operations to start in 2029.
data.description: A deal has been finalized between Competitive Power Ventures (CPV) and the Public Utility Commission of Texas (PUCT) for a $1.1 billion low-interest loan from the Texas Energy Fund (TxEF). The loan is designated for the construction of a massive 1,350-megawatt combined-cycle natural gas power plant in the Permian Basin. Construction on the CPV Basin Ranch Energy Center in Ward County will begin promptly, aiming to commence operations by 2029. This project stands as the most substantial one chosen thus far for financial backing through TxEF.

data.title: Intersect names Katrina Rymill as CFO, with 20 years experience in tech finance. Will drive growth for data centers with energy solutions.
data.description: San Francisco-based company, Intersect, has named Katrina Rymill as its new Chief Financial Officer. With over 20 years of experience in financial leadership within rapidly growing technology firms, Rymill joins the company to enhance strategic growth initiatives. Previously working at Equinix, Rymill is expected to aid in amplifying Intersect's developments in co-locating data centers alongside specialized gas and renewable power solutions. This appointment signifies a pivotal move for Intersect's future endeavors.

data.title: Doug Uhlenbrock appointed as new Executive Director of Family RV Association in Cincinnati, effective immediately.
data.description: A new executive director, Doug Uhlenbrock, has been appointed at the Family RV Association in Cincinnati on October 30, 2025. This announcement came following the unanimous approval of his appointment by the association's Executive Board. Uhlenbrock, a longstanding employee of the organization, will assume his role with immediate effect. Previously named as the Family Motor, the Association holds a significant position within the industry.

data.title: Prosafe's Safe Caledonia extended at Captain field in UK North Sea until mid-December 2025 by Ithaca Energy for approx USD 1.8 million.
data.description: On 30 October 2025, Ithaca Energy (UK) Limited (‘Ithaca’) has chosen to extend the accommodation support provided by the Safe Caledonia at the Captain field in the UK North Sea sector for an additional two (2) weeks, extending the contract through to mid-December 2025. Ithaca retains the option for a further ten (10) weeks. The value of this contract extension amounts to around USD 1.8 million. Prosafe, a prominent owner and operator of semi-submersible accommodation vessels, facilitates this service. Prosafe is publicly listed on the Oslo Stock Exchange under the ticker code PRS. For further details, visit www.prosafe.com.

data.title: AdminaHealth maintains 99% client retention with a +70 NPS score, surpassing industry standards amid increased vendor switching for cost reasons.
data.description: Recent data from WTW indicates an increase in vendor switching as a result of rising costs. Despite this trend, AdminaHealth has stood out for its reliability, impressive return on investment, and top-notch data security measures. Based in Greenwich, Conn., the company has established itself as a pioneer in automated premium billing solutions. The report was released on October 30, 2025, highlighting the noteworthy achievements of AdminaHealth in the industry.

data.title: Ambev's Q3 profit up 8.7% Y/Y, shares rise; earnings at 24 cents per share in Brazilian Reals ($3.826 billion in sales).
data.description: Shares of Ambev SA (NYSE: ABEV) rose after the company announced its third-quarter FY25 results. The company reported earnings of 24 cents per share in Brazilian Reals (equivalent to 4 cents per share in USD), marking an 8.7% increase year over year. This growth was attributed to lower taxes. Quarterly sales stood at 20.8 billion Brazilian Real ($3.826 billion), a 5.7% decrease compared to the previous year. Normalized EBITDA increased by 2.9% Y/Y organically, with margins expanding by 50 basis points. The full story can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Chevron and Exxon Mobil set to report Q3 earnings and revenue before stock market open, potential for consistency.
data.description: Before the stock market opened on Friday, Chevron and Exxon Mobil revealed their earnings and revenue for the third quarter. Investors were curious if the results would maintain the trend seen in previous quarters for the two supermajors.

data.title: Roblox's stock fell despite beating Q3 expectations and raising guidance. Stock took hit post-report.
data.description: Roblox, an online platform popular among kids, performed better than expected in the third quarter and provided a positive outlook for the current period. However, despite these successes, the stock of Roblox experienced a decline. The report on Roblox's third-quarter performance with exceeding figures contrasted with the drop in its stock value was featured on Investor's Business Daily.

data.title: CoreWeave terminates deal with Core Scientific after shareholders reject merger offer, causing stock to fall.
data.description: CoreWeave experienced a decline in its stock price following the cancellation of its acquisition by "neocloud" due to the rejection of the merger offer by its shareholders. The termination of the deal between CoreWeave and Core Scientific was announced recently. This decision resulted in a negative impact on CoreWeave's financial standing as indicated by the decrease in its stock value. The rejected offer and subsequent termination have significant implications for both companies involved, impacting their future business strategies and potential growth opportunities. However, the exact numbers related to the stock fall and financial implications were not provided in the summarized information.

data.title: Biogen faces setbacks as key growth drivers hit snags in the third quarter, causing stock to slightly decline.
data.description: In the third quarter, Biogen faced challenges with two key drivers of growth. This led to fluctuations in the company's stock, with a recent slight decline. Despite this, the issues were not considered fundamental problems.

data.title: Eli Lilly beats Q3 forecasts with stock rising; two main drugs contributing; strong performance praised.
data.description: Eli Lilly's stock saw an early surge on Thursday following the release of their third-quarter financial results, where the company exceeded expectations. This was driven by the success of their two leading drugs. The performance was described as one of the best in the quarter.

data.title: Crocs repurchased 2.4 million shares, paid off $63 million debt, beating Q3 earnings with $2.92 EPS, sales $996.301M.
data.description: Crocs, Inc. (NASDAQ: CROX) shares rose after CEO Andrew Rees shared that strong profitability and cash flow enabled the company to buy back 2.4 million shares and reduce $63 million in debt last quarter. Despite this, CROX stock displayed weakness and surrendered its initial gains following the third-quarter earnings report. For the third quarter, the company reported adjusted earnings per share of $2.92, surpassing the analyst consensus of $2.36. Their quarterly sales of $996.301 million (down 6.2% year over year) exceeded the Street's expectation of $962.546 million. Crocs brand revenue declined. Further details are available on Benzinga.com.
